3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) - The paper uses analytical methods to solve the minimum dominating set problem in two specific graphs, which can be considered as a numerical analysis problem. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) - The paper discusses the domination number and minimum dominating sets in graphs, which are important concepts in game theory.
